CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 28, 1953, pg. 1, reads: "Lifeguard? Because of a threatened shortage of male applicants for city and county lifeguard jobs, there's a possibility that good-looking and shapely Fannie McDaniel, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Henry J. McDaniel, 5641 Eva Street, may get a job at one of the county pools this year. At least she has been allowed to file her application and has been preparing to qualify by practice at the Centre Avenue YMCA swimming pool. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Lifeguard applicant Fannie McDaniel wearing two-piece bathing suit and seated on diving board in Centre Avenue YMCA swimming pool
